  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "For performance reasons, the headers that Envoy uses internally are stored inline in the Http::HeaderMap implementation. Appending values is not supported for these headers. The v2 API, however, allows them to be configured for append or replace at various levels (see #2003).\r\n\r\nCurrently, requests to append values are ignored and the header value is simply replaced. It can be argued that even this should not be allowed.\r\n\r\nNeed to determine whether modification of the inline headers via API config is allowed. If not, write validation code to prevent it. If allowed, consider whether specifying values to append is a configuration error or should just be ignored. The chosen behavior and the list of inline headers should be documented.\r\n",
